    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a Medium model risk / Medium decision consequence context. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 1 vs. required Gradation 2) is accepted because the ASTM F1717 standard specifies a single canonical test configuration and all quantitative output comparison metrics are well within acceptance bounds for all three QoIs. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision.",
